1
00:01:36,630 --> 00:01:39,870
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:41,970
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:50,520
Fenghua is busy and doesn't have time to see you.

4
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:51,350
-Fenghua.
-Fenghua.

5
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,070
Fenghua.

6
00:01:52,090 --> 00:01:53,090
Fenghua!

7
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:53,930
Fenghua.

8
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:55,009
Sorry, Fenghua.

9
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:56,759
We want to quit too.

10
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,490
Have you all thought it through?

11
00:02:02,670 --> 00:02:03,750
Yes.

12
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,330
Even if it means delivering over 50 more orders a day?

13
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:09,229
We're not afraid of hard work.

14
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:10,759
We're afraid of poverty.

15
00:02:11,790 --> 00:02:12,720
Please don't overthink it.

16
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,220
Nowadays,

17
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,560
everyone out there is doing the same.

18
00:02:16,110 --> 00:02:17,130
The workload

19
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,250
is getting bigger day by day.

20
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:19,430
We...

21
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,340
We know you're considerate.

22
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,180
We just want to make money.

23
00:02:31,270 --> 00:02:32,070
I see.

24
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:34,900
Making money is not a problem.

25
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,579
But don't push yourself too hard.

26
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:37,660
Try not to get sick.

27
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:39,570
Hospitals are expensive here.

28
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:42,829
He,

29
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,050
help settle their accounts.

30
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,430
Fenghua, this...

31
00:02:46,829 --> 00:02:47,930
-Thank you, Fenghua.
-Thank you, Fenghua.

32
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:48,710
Thank you, Fenghua.

33
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:52,030
You guys...

34
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:42,340
Are you crazy?

35
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,370
It's your own shoe, don't blame me.

36
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,040
I was wondering why everyone had left.

37
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:48,910
No, no, no.

38
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:50,430
Alright, alright.

39
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:51,920
Let me tell you some good news.

40
00:03:53,070 --> 00:03:54,540
Our overtime rate

41
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:56,710
has been controlled at five percent.

42
00:03:56,829 --> 00:03:57,780
Really?

43
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:00,140
Let's have a late-night snack to celebrate.

44
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:02,200
You two can celebrate.

45
00:04:02,230 --> 00:04:03,720
I'm going home to catch up on sleep.

46
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:04,860
I'll wake you up.

47
00:04:06,380 --> 00:04:07,940
Quick, quick, just smell this and you'll wake up.

48
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:08,840
Take it away.

49
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,660
Let's eat together and then go sleep.

50
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,090
Come on, let's go.

51
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,530
I'm not going, really not going.

52
00:04:16,170 --> 00:04:17,510
You're really not going?

53
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:19,399
Who is it at this late hour?

54
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,029
Must be a woman.

55
00:04:22,790 --> 00:04:23,790
Oh, Fenghua.

56
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:28,060
Are you free tomorrow? I'd like to treat you to coffee.

57
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:32,090
Why won't she invite me for coffee?

58
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,960
I'm free. You can tell her that.

59
00:04:35,990 --> 00:04:37,230
I'm leaving. I'm going home to sleep.

60
00:04:39,790 --> 00:04:41,110
Let's go together!

61
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:42,190
Hurry up, hurry up.

62
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:48,680
How have you been doing lately?

63
00:04:49,470 --> 00:04:50,510
Not bad.

64
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:52,550
I'm the expert canvasser.

65
00:04:52,590 --> 00:04:55,120
I went there and impressed them all in just a couple of days.

66
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:57,830
Is Wanghe treating you well?

67
00:04:58,060 --> 00:04:59,550
His attitude is impeccable,

68
00:04:59,580 --> 00:05:01,050
but I haven't seen any money yet.

69
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:02,590
However, I bet

70
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:03,750
it'll be good.

71
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:08,110
You didn't discuss payment before starting work? You're something else.

72
00:05:08,420 --> 00:05:10,200
That's Xie Wanghe.

73
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,650
Would he cheat me?

74
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,820
What a joke.

75
00:05:14,670 --> 00:05:16,870
Asking a girl out for coffee during work hours.

76
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,000
Is that appropriate?

77
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,870
Sorry, boss.

78
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:22,930
It was love at first sight on the street.

79
00:05:23,450 --> 00:05:25,350
Love at first sight?

80
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,280
Waiter.

81
00:05:32,090 --> 00:05:33,120
Bring a cup of coffee.

82
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:34,590
And an afternoon tea set as well.

83
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:35,510
Certainly, please wait a moment.

84
00:05:38,050 --> 00:05:39,100
Ms. Xia,

85
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,900
is business not good?

86
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,330
You still have time for coffee?

87
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:44,900
I'm here to poach someone.

88
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:47,730
Xingchi.

89
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:49,280
Come work for me.

90
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:53,620
Dream on.

91
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:56,010
We have a labor contract.

92
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:59,000
If you want to poach him, pay the compensation first.

93
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:00,140
How much is it?

94
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,230
You're really serious about poaching?

95
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,910
I'm really short-staffed lately.

96
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,160
If he could come, it would save me a lot of trouble.

97
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,050
Where have you been?

98
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:15,080
To poach someone, you've got to strike first.

99
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,720
It's too late now.

100
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:19,300
I offer insurance and housing fund. Does he?

101
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:23,150
Wait...

102
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:24,330
You're being serious?

103
00:06:24,370 --> 00:06:25,400
I'm serious.

104
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,940
I'm exhausted now. I can't handle it anymore.

105
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:38,540
Fenghua,

106
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:40,460
how about this?

107
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:42,210
I'll subsidize you.

108
00:06:42,370 --> 00:06:43,620
Poach a professional,

109
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,520
someone with management experience.

110
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:46,659
If you pay enough,

111
00:06:46,690 --> 00:06:48,050
you won't have trouble finding someone.

112
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,730
I've just got things sorted out here.

113
00:06:50,210 --> 00:06:51,480
I can't give you Xingchi.

114
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:53,300
I'm sorry.

115
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:11,800
[Fenghua Express]

116
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:11,020
Fenghua.

117
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:12,720
Thank you.

118
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:22,050
Why aren't you eating?

119
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,020
I don't have an appetite.

120
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,180
Are you really childhood friends with Mr. Xie and them?

121
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,300
Why? Doesn't seem like it?

122
00:07:32,470 --> 00:07:33,490
Are you close?

123
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:36,940
Of course. We grew up in the same courtyard.

124
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:38,490
Door to door, window to window.

125
00:07:38,530 --> 00:07:40,600
We could even hear each other sleep talking at night.

126
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:42,300
Then why do they treat you like that?

127
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,770
Are you trying to sow discord now?

128
00:07:46,790 --> 00:07:48,060
No, no, no.

129
00:07:55,230 --> 00:07:56,860
He, call the ambulance!

130
00:07:57,770 --> 00:07:58,350
Fenghua.

131
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:00,550
Take a rest! Look at your condition!

132
00:08:00,570 --> 00:08:02,770
Don't worry, we're here. Nothing will be lost.

133
00:08:05,870 --> 00:08:06,510
Fenghua!

134
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:11,030
Don't run!

135
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:11,870
Get out of the way!

136
00:08:11,890 --> 00:08:13,990
It's none of your business. Move aside, move aside!

137
00:08:14,010 --> 00:08:15,700
He, note down the license plate number.

138
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:16,520
Move aside, move aside!

139
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:17,350
Let me tell you,

140
00:08:17,380 --> 00:08:20,180
if you dare to run, it's a hit-and-run. You'll be sentenced.

141
00:08:20,210 --> 00:08:21,180
See that?

142
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:23,510
There are cameras over there.

143
00:08:23,530 --> 00:08:24,920
Run off to outer space if you can.

144
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:25,910
I've gotten it, Fenghua.

145
00:08:25,350 --> 00:08:25,800
[Shuntong Express]

146
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,190
Mr. Wei.

147
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:40,929
How is it?

148
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,400
The driver is over there.

149
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,820
The traffic police are taking notes.

150
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:44,800
What about the courier?

151
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:45,750
Sent to the hospital.

152
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:46,670
He fractured his lower leg.

153
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:47,770
The rest still needs to be examined.

154
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,210
Don't worry.

155
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,180
We kept an eye on it. Nothing's missing.

156
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,510
It's just this box.

157
00:08:55,590 --> 00:08:56,990
You might need to pay compensation.

158
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:01,510
Here, cigarette.

159
00:09:07,940 --> 00:09:09,300
It's fortunate you were here.

160
00:09:10,230 --> 00:09:11,110
We're all in the same business.

161
00:09:11,130 --> 00:09:12,370
No need for such formalities.

162
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:13,970
If there's nothing else, we'll be going now.

163
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:16,380
You can discuss the accident settlement with the traffic police.

164
00:09:18,730 --> 00:09:24,330
[Steamed Buns]

165
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:21,340
Fenghua,

166
00:09:21,370 --> 00:09:22,510
are we just leaving like this?

167
00:09:22,530 --> 00:09:24,850
What else? Wait for him to pay you?

168
00:09:25,110 --> 00:09:26,760
He didn't even say thank you.

169
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:29,460
It doesn't make a difference whether he says it or not.

170
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,000
As long as he thinks it, it's fine.

171
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:31,980
I'm afraid he doesn't.

172
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,560
He'll just play dumb and let it slide.

173
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:36,000
It doesn't matter. Just take it as doing a good deed.

174
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:37,620
What would you like to eat? It's my treat.

175
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,080
What are you thinking about?

176
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:57,310
Nothing.

177
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,890
Worried about Fenghua?

178
00:10:08,890 --> 00:10:10,930
She always shares the good news but never the bad.

179
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:13,760
This is the first time she's surrendered

180
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:15,010
and said she's tired.

181
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:20,740
How much pressure can there be in the express delivery industry?

182
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:22,850
If she can't handle it,

183
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:24,390
she should just reduce the delivery areas.

184
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,610
Fenghua has quite a few people working under her.

185
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:28,890
If she can't afford to pay them, she should fire them.

186
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:32,170
She's running an express delivery business, not a charity.

187
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:33,550
She's soft-hearted.

188
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:34,690
She likes to take on everything.

189
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,790
She spoils all her subordinates.

190
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,840
Everyone says she's nice.

191
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,470
She bears all the pressure alone.

192
00:10:39,490 --> 00:10:40,780
This can't go on forever.

193
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:43,760
If she wants to bear it, let her.

194
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:44,910
When she can't handle it anymore,

195
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:45,950
she'll naturally let it go.

196
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,950
When that time comes, we'll help her

197
00:10:48,990 --> 00:10:50,070
with whatever she needs.

198
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:52,110
We'll make sure she doesn't suffer or go poor.

199
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:53,730
But she's feeling wronged right now.

200
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,070
That's her own doing.

201
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,440
When I went to Bee,

202
00:10:59,470 --> 00:11:00,820
I wanted her to come with me.

203
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,700
The salary would have been much higher than now.

204
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:03,510
With me there,

205
00:11:03,570 --> 00:11:05,180
I could have taken care of her if anything happened.

206
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,490
She absolutely refused to do it.

207
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,150
Why?

208
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:08,820
Because she couldn't let go of those employees.

209
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:11,210
And what happened?

210
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:13,820
Other companies offered 300 yuan more per month,

211
00:11:14,030 --> 00:11:16,390
and those people left without a second thought.

212
00:11:17,050 --> 00:11:18,420
Fenghua got wasted

213
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,960
and came to my doorstep at night, sobbing,

214
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,670
asking me how much she was worth.

215
00:11:23,130 --> 00:11:25,330
Why was 300 yuan was enough to betray her?

216
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,610
What could I have said?

217
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:28,780
It was her own fault?

218
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,680
♫When I need someone the most♫

219
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:42,780
♫Gently pat on my shoulder♫

220
00:11:43,310 --> 00:11:45,440
♫Who is willing to share with me♫

221
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:48,040
♫In their happiest moments?♫

222
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:50,880
♫Life is long♫

223
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:53,780
♫I'm by your side♫

224
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:55,850
♫Witnessing your growth♫

225
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:59,590
♫Gives me strength♫

226
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:57,550
Hello?

227
00:11:57,910 --> 00:11:58,580
What are you doing?

228
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,310
♫Who can forget the past?♫

229
00:12:00,210 --> 00:12:01,200
On a date.

230
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:02,090
A date?

231
00:12:02,170 --> 00:12:05,190
♫I've been with you all the way♫

232
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:04,270
Is there someone in your room?

233
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:07,380
♫Who can predict the future?♫

234
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:08,390
Fine.

235
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,870
♫Long and far, where are you?♫

236
00:12:08,890 --> 00:12:09,470
I'm leaving.

237
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:14,590
Where are you going?

238
00:12:25,690 --> 00:12:27,010
I've figured it out.

239
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:29,510
You're the biggest obstacle in my weight loss journey.

240
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:30,470
You've always been.

241
00:12:30,490 --> 00:12:31,300
Fine.

242
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:33,090
Don't eat it.

243
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:33,930
I'll eat it.

244
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:36,960
Hand it over.

245
00:12:37,370 --> 00:12:38,070
Go away.

246
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:44,700
You're not mad at me, are you?

247
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:45,960
I am.

248
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:48,290
You're pregnant?

249
00:12:48,770 --> 00:12:50,490
How long has it been? How many months?

250
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:53,950
It's burning my eyes.

251
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,750
Serves you right for making me angry.

252
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:56,660
Get me some tissues.

253
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,460
Actually, I'm quite happy for you.

254
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:06,260
What are you happy about?

255
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,210
At least you've settled down

256
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,050
and are willing to do some proper work.

257
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:12,090
We were all worried about you before.

258
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,920
Xie Wanghe begged me.

259
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:20,890
I had to give him some respect, at least.

260
00:13:21,430 --> 00:13:23,000
I begged you too.

261
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:24,470
But you didn't give me respect.

262
00:13:33,210 --> 00:13:34,900
Wanghe is indeed having a tough time now.

263
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:36,000
He's under a lot of pressure.

264
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:38,520
Now, everyone in the company

265
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:39,800
is waiting for him to fail.

266
00:13:40,540 --> 00:13:41,900
I went over with Haikuo

267
00:13:42,340 --> 00:13:43,270
to help him.

268
00:13:45,140 --> 00:13:46,360
Once we get through this busy period,

269
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,410
and overcome this hurdle,

270
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:50,180
the road ahead will be smoother.

271
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,030
Don't be mad at me.

272
00:13:59,030 --> 00:14:01,250
As soon as I finish canvassing the east street,

273
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:02,470
I'll come help you when I have time.

274
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,080
No need.

275
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,130
I'm not really tired,

276
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:09,290
just anxious.

277
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:10,740
What are you anxious about?

278
00:14:12,550 --> 00:14:14,470
Food delivery is booming right now.

279
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,180
They're pouring money into recruitment.

280
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,910
I'm afraid I'll wake up one day

281
00:14:18,050 --> 00:14:19,050
and all my employees will be gone.

282
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:24,670
Let them go.

283
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,090
You can't keep the ones you want to stay.

284
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,470
You can't force away the ones you want to leave.

285
00:14:27,890 --> 00:14:28,660
Just let it be.

286
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:34,680
Keep an eye on Wanghe.

287
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,190
Don't let him do anything reckless.

288
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:37,670
He's the type who's willing to do anything

289
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,980
for the sake of performance.

290
00:14:39,610 --> 00:14:41,640
When he was doing ground promotions with Haikuo before,

291
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:43,980
he dared to climb over the wall into a school in broad daylight.

292
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:45,900
He almost fell to his death when the security guards chased him.

293
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:52,570
If you have time to worry about others,

294
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:56,170
why don't you take good care of yourself instead?

295
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:57,740
I'm doing fine.

296
00:14:57,850 --> 00:14:58,730
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

297
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:01,790
Then don't get upset in the future,

298
00:15:01,830 --> 00:15:04,380
and complain after getting drunk at midnight.

299
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,620
You talk so much every day.

300
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:18,340
I'll do it myself.

301
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:25,250
You're full?

302
00:15:34,860 --> 00:15:38,290
[Fenghua Express]

303
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,950
You turned smart today.

304
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,340
You even remembered to lock it.

305
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:48,100
[Fenghua Express]

306
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,850
It's okay, you go up and deliver it.

307
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:51,870
I'll watch it for you.

308
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:53,590
Really. You can go.

309
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:58,830
The packages are all here.

310
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,520
I dare you to touch it.

311
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:05,900
I touched it.

312
00:16:05,920 --> 00:16:06,820
So what?

313
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:08,090
You gonna bite me?

314
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:11,010
Don't be shameless when I'm being nice.

315
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:13,090
What if I am shameless?

316
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:14,720
Being shameless, huh?

317
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:15,770
Being shameless, huh?

318
00:16:15,860 --> 00:16:16,630
Come on.

319
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:33,980
Are you hurt?

320
00:16:35,420 --> 00:16:36,180
No.

321
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:37,690
Where are they?

322
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:39,280
They're inside.

323
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,570
I didn't fight.

324
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,400
That's progress.

325
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,640
He threw my packages.

326
00:16:44,660 --> 00:16:46,170
They're all fragile items inside.

327
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:47,460
They must compensate for that.

328
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,240
We will.

329
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:52,220
We were in the wrong this time.

330
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:54,370
We'll compensate for whatever is damaged.

331
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:08,170
Come, sit down.

332
00:17:08,230 --> 00:17:08,839
Why are you standing?

333
00:17:08,859 --> 00:17:10,300
Have a seat. Have some water.

334
00:17:09,150 --> 00:17:12,589
[Shuntong Express]

335
00:17:10,329 --> 00:17:11,250
Thank you.

336
00:17:11,910 --> 00:17:12,800
No need.

337
00:17:12,819 --> 00:17:14,859
I should be thanking you.

338
00:17:14,890 --> 00:17:16,380
About that incident last time,

339
00:17:16,730 --> 00:17:18,960
if you hadn't been there,

340
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:22,980
I would've been in big trouble if I'd lost that package.

341
00:17:23,859 --> 00:17:25,460
You should advise them in the future

342
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:27,290
to always wear helmets when riding.

343
00:17:27,329 --> 00:17:28,700
I've already told them.

344
00:17:28,730 --> 00:17:29,910
And I've made it a rule.

345
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:31,510
If you don't wear a helmet, you'll be fined.

346
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:32,640
They think it's too hot.

347
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:33,850
Well...

348
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:36,490
Did you buy insurance for them?

349
00:17:36,550 --> 00:17:37,510
Yes, I did.

350
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:39,620
Three yuan a day for accident insurance.

351
00:17:40,020 --> 00:17:41,140
Three yuan?

352
00:17:41,170 --> 00:17:42,320
That's not enough.

353
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:49,610
I won't worry about your company's affairs.

354
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:51,340
How about

355
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:52,520
we talk about business?

356
00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:53,980
Rather than vicious competition,

357
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:55,350
it's better to cooperate for mutual benefit.

358
00:17:55,370 --> 00:17:56,690
How do you want to cooperate?

359
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,830
I'll take the east side, you take the west.

360
00:17:58,850 --> 00:18:00,020
We each do our own thing.

361
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:02,870
The Keyuan Nanli community in the middle has the highest volume of deliveries.

362
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,370
We can work together there

363
00:18:04,390 --> 00:18:05,470
and split the profits proportionally.

364
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,760
We won't take advantage of you.

365
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:09,040
A 40-60 split.

366
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,440
Our two companies can cover this entire area.

367
00:18:13,510 --> 00:18:14,950
Other big companies won't be able to get in.

368
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:17,750
30-70 split.

369
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,150
Look, I have so many people.

370
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,110
The pressure is high.

371
00:18:25,430 --> 00:18:26,220
Alright.

372
00:18:26,330 --> 00:18:27,330
Then 30-70 it is.

373
00:18:29,220 --> 00:18:30,290
It's a pleasure doing business with you.

374
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:31,260
Please take care of us.

375
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:32,660
[Shelf 04]

376
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:44,030
[EV charging is prohibited in the workshop and warehouse]

377
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,300
You scared me.

378
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:48,250
[No smoking]

379
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,220
It was going so well.

380
00:18:46,310 --> 00:18:47,270
Why did you bring up insurance?

381
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:48,920
You said three yuan wasn't enough.

382
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:50,340
Mr. Wei almost lost his temper.

383
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:51,770
It really isn't enough.

384
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:58,470
[Be careful of fire]

385
00:18:51,820 --> 00:18:52,790
How much can insurance

386
00:18:52,790 --> 00:18:54,830
for three yuan a day pay if an accident happens?

387
00:18:56,290 --> 00:18:56,900
Fenghua,

388
00:18:57,210 --> 00:18:58,730
the wool comes from the sheep's back.

389
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:02,420
[Shuntong Express]

390
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:00,280
Rather than spending money on peace of mind,

391
00:19:00,510 --> 00:19:02,120
it's better to increase everyone's commission.

392
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,730
That's narrow-minded.

393
00:19:04,950 --> 00:19:06,030
Everyone thinks that way.

394
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,070
Really.

395
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:15,040
He is back.

396
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:17,270
Mr. He, how was the talk?

397
00:19:15,620 --> 00:19:20,800
[Fenghua Express]

398
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,790
How did it go?

399
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:20,970
You're all eating?

400
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:22,300
-Fenghua.
-Fenghua.

401
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:23,220
-Fenghua.
-Fenghua.

402
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:25,560
First, I have some good news for everyone.

403
00:19:25,710 --> 00:19:26,970
I've already communicated

404
00:19:27,090 --> 00:19:28,770
with Mr. Wei from Shuntong.

405
00:19:28,790 --> 00:19:30,330
From now on, we'll work together

406
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:31,600
in Keyuan Nanli.

407
00:19:31,630 --> 00:19:32,870
There won't be any more business disputes.

408
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:34,870
Great!

409
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:37,390
There's one more thing I want to discuss with everyone.

410
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:39,860
Okay, go ahead. Tell us.

411
00:19:39,890 --> 00:19:42,020
I've tried to get insurance.

412
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:43,580
The headquarters said there's no such plan,

413
00:19:43,770 --> 00:19:47,120
so I hope everyone can work together.

414
00:19:47,150 --> 00:19:48,070
I'll pay half,

415
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:49,290
and everyone pays the other half.

416
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,920
Let's buy the basic five insurances and one housing fund.

417
00:19:57,170 --> 00:19:58,170
I know

418
00:19:58,830 --> 00:20:00,680
everyone is reluctant to spend this money.

419
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,540
You think it's useless.

420
00:20:01,540 --> 00:20:02,880
It really is useless.

421
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,750
We came to Beijing to make money.

422
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:05,980
We can't stay here anyway.

423
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,120
Once we've earned enough money,

424
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:08,800
most of us still have to go back home, right?

425
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:10,180
Yes, indeed.

426
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,520
It's the same for me.

427
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:13,750
I came to Beijing right after graduating from high school.

428
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:14,990
Over these six or seven years,

429
00:20:15,020 --> 00:20:16,810
I've changed countless jobs.

430
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:17,920
Why is that?

431
00:20:18,110 --> 00:20:20,060
I just felt unsettled inside.

432
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:21,210
I didn't have a sense of belonging.

433
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:22,400
So I hope

434
00:20:22,420 --> 00:20:23,940
we can all work together

435
00:20:23,970 --> 00:20:25,310
to get the insurances

436
00:20:25,350 --> 00:20:26,110
and make our place

437
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:28,330
a home we can rely on.

438
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,460
It's okay.

439
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:45,850
Think about it some more.

440
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,800
I'm not forcing the insurance issue.

441
00:20:47,820 --> 00:20:50,230
Those who want it can fill out the application form.

442
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:51,330
You all eat up.

443
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:58,870
Mr. Wang, these couriers are out doing deliveries all day.

444
00:20:58,910 --> 00:21:00,850
What if an accident happens one day?

445
00:21:01,230 --> 00:21:02,150
Currently, we're

446
00:21:02,150 --> 00:21:04,110
deducting money from their wages to buy accident insurance.

447
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:06,620
But precisely because it's their own money being deducted,

448
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,220
they don't want to buy it.

449
00:21:08,790 --> 00:21:10,110
So, I was thinking,

450
00:21:10,130 --> 00:21:11,330
if I cover half

451
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:12,670
and the company covers the other half,

452
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:14,810
they won't have to pay for it.

453
00:21:14,850 --> 00:21:15,530
What are you thinking?

454
00:21:17,460 --> 00:21:19,310
How many employees do we have in our company?

455
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:20,840
If I cover half for them,

456
00:21:20,860 --> 00:21:22,370
half for all the people, in our company,

457
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:23,200
how will we survive?

458
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,600
You're trying to bankrupt the company, aren't you?

459
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:26,630
Let me tell you,

460
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,630
this method you're suggesting is absolutely impossible.

461
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,310
Alright.

462
00:21:30,540 --> 00:21:31,330
I understand.

463
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,760
Let's leave it at that for now.

464
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:54,200
[Data Center]

465
00:21:54,200 --> 00:22:02,820
[Send] [Take]

466
00:21:56,700 --> 00:21:57,550
Does it feel good to see?

467
00:21:58,900 --> 00:21:59,700
It's okay.

468
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:03,010
Just keep pretending.

469
00:22:03,370 --> 00:22:04,370
Really.

470
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:06,700
It's just a few kilometers of territory.

471
00:22:07,370 --> 00:22:09,070
They couldn't handle it before

472
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:10,240
because they were incompetent.

473
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:11,600
I'm complimenting you.

474
00:22:11,770 --> 00:22:13,210
Don't give others a hard time.

475
00:22:13,390 --> 00:22:15,330
I'm not giving anyone a hard time.

476
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,160
I'm just being practical.

477
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:20,650
Prioritize the bigger picture.

478
00:22:26,510 --> 00:22:27,530
You did well this time.

479
00:22:27,570 --> 00:22:28,450
You didn't embarrass me.

480
00:22:29,900 --> 00:22:30,870
Don't just say it.

481
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,970
How about contributing that bottle of Fenjiu?

482
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,260
You're not drinking it anyway.

483
00:22:35,670 --> 00:22:36,460
Liquor?

484
00:22:36,630 --> 00:22:37,340
Take it if you want.

485
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:39,830
This is for you too.

486
00:22:42,810 --> 00:22:43,690
Really giving it to me?

487
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:45,290
This is just the beginning.

488
00:22:45,910 --> 00:22:47,960
If you help me secure Haidian District,

489
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:49,110
I have a big reward for you later.

490
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:55,420
Wait for my good news.

491
00:23:35,540 --> 00:23:36,520
This month,

492
00:23:35,630 --> 00:23:41,630
[Service Counter]

493
00:23:37,310 --> 00:23:38,850
everyone has done a great job.

494
00:23:39,450 --> 00:23:41,850
Our order volume has repeatedly hit new highs.

495
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:44,080
Under Mr. Xie's leadership,

496
00:23:44,210 --> 00:23:47,260
you've created miracles for Bee.

497
00:23:47,740 --> 00:23:49,110
Mr. Xie's rule is

498
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:51,110
clear rewards and punishments.

499
00:23:51,550 --> 00:23:53,290
It has proven to be effective.

500
00:23:54,610 --> 00:23:55,780
I've thought about it

501
00:23:56,390 --> 00:23:58,460
and decided that next week's commission

502
00:23:58,870 --> 00:23:59,980
will be doubled!

503
00:24:03,030 --> 00:24:05,950
Mr. Xie!

504
00:24:05,970 --> 00:24:08,760
Mr. Xie!

505
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:11,640
Mr. Xie!

506
00:24:11,670 --> 00:24:14,440
Mr. Xie!

507
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:17,140
Mr. Xie!

508
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:27,250
What's wrong with you?

509
00:24:27,430 --> 00:24:29,310
Are things not going well at work?

510
00:24:33,890 --> 00:24:35,800
A few more employees jumped ship today

511
00:24:36,370 --> 00:24:37,340
to Bee.

512
00:24:38,070 --> 00:24:39,190
Why?

513
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,100
It pays better than this.

514
00:24:46,030 --> 00:24:47,460
You can't leave.

515
00:24:48,690 --> 00:24:50,640
Ms. Xia has been good to our family.

516
00:24:50,810 --> 00:24:52,250
As long as she's here,

517
00:24:54,030 --> 00:24:55,280
we can't leave.

518
00:24:55,530 --> 00:24:56,300
Got it?

519
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,850
Stop drinking.

520
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,110
Stop drinking. You've been at it all night.

521
00:25:04,150 --> 00:25:05,340
I'm afraid if she still doesn't think of a way,

522
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:06,410
we'll have to close too.

523
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:09,470
When that happens,

524
00:25:11,030 --> 00:25:12,020
what are we going to do?

525
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:14,610
Our whole family will end up living under a bridge.

526
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:21,880
When I first came to Beijing,

527
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:24,150
I loved seeing the lights from all the households.

528
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:26,960
I thought that as long as I worked hard,

529
00:25:27,260 --> 00:25:28,630
one day,

530
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:30,270
I could have

531
00:25:30,350 --> 00:25:32,000
my own home here too.

532
00:25:35,790 --> 00:25:36,850
But

533
00:25:37,310 --> 00:25:39,150
after working hard all these years,

534
00:25:39,780 --> 00:25:40,700
I realized that

535
00:25:40,710 --> 00:25:43,520
in this place that seems to have infinite possibilities,

536
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,660
everyone is being held hostage

537
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:48,400
by cruel competition.

538
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:52,870
As for me,

539
00:25:54,130 --> 00:25:56,360
I'm just an insignificant person.

540
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:59,280
I can't change anything.

541
00:26:12,770 --> 00:26:13,560
Wanghe.

542
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,270
Mr. Meng.

543
00:26:14,270 --> 00:26:16,750
I've brought you the liquor you wanted.

544
00:26:16,860 --> 00:26:18,220
You're really willing to give it to me?

545
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:19,140
What are you talking about?

546
00:26:19,170 --> 00:26:20,320
I've even given you the car.

547
00:26:20,350 --> 00:26:21,720
A bottle of liquor is nothing.

548
00:26:22,110 --> 00:26:22,860
From now on,

549
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,180
just take whatever you like.

550
00:26:25,410 --> 00:26:26,680
As long as you all can help me

551
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,730
completely take over Haidian District,

552
00:26:28,770 --> 00:26:29,740
I'll even drive you all

553
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:31,330
to and from work every day if you want.

554
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:32,710
I wouldn't dare.

555
00:26:33,310 --> 00:26:34,550
Then let's wait

556
00:26:35,150 --> 00:26:36,640
until we've completely taken over Haidian

557
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:37,720
and drink this at the celebration party.

558
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:38,510
Alright.

559
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:41,430
Let me formally introduce you all.

560
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:43,150
Zhou Haikuo.

561
00:26:43,180 --> 00:26:44,370
Shao Xingchi.

562
00:26:44,410 --> 00:26:45,070
Hello.

563
00:26:45,090 --> 00:26:45,620
Mr. Meng.

564
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:47,340
Hello.

