642
00:30:08,780 --> 00:30:10,050
Okay, let's not talk about it.

643
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:11,930
Let's sing and drink.

644
00:30:55,950 --> 00:30:57,100
What are you doing?

645
00:30:57,810 --> 00:30:59,090
Are you stealing oil?

646
00:31:00,590 --> 00:31:01,480
Stop!

647
00:31:01,850 --> 00:31:03,230
How dare you steal oil?

648
00:31:04,220 --> 00:31:05,060
Stop!

649
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,500
Stop!

650
00:31:07,310 --> 00:31:08,740
How dare you steal oil?

651
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:10,180
You dare to steal oil?

652
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,360
Boss!

653
00:31:13,380 --> 00:31:14,750
You dare to steal oil!

654
00:31:17,830 --> 00:31:19,390
Go, go, go!

655
00:31:22,150 --> 00:31:23,060
Little rascals!

656
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:24,060
Stealing oil?

657
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:35,800
Boss, what's wrong?

658
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:37,800
I was too careless.

659
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:39,890
Help!

660
00:31:40,460 --> 00:31:41,750
Help!

661
00:31:41,780 --> 00:31:42,770
Help!

662
00:31:43,390 --> 00:31:45,520
Someone, help!

663
00:31:53,890 --> 00:31:54,610
Mom?

664
00:31:58,550 --> 00:31:59,570
Is he okay?

665
00:32:01,070 --> 00:32:02,110
Okay, okay, I got it.

666
00:32:02,150 --> 00:32:02,950
I'll be right there.

667
00:32:03,540 --> 00:32:04,100
What happened?

668
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:05,940
My dad was stabbed while driving long-distance.

669
00:32:05,970 --> 00:32:07,290
He's in emergency care at Tianjin Hospital now.

670
00:32:07,310 --> 00:32:08,310
I need to get there quickly.

671
00:32:11,170 --> 00:32:12,340
You've been drinking. How can you drive?

672
00:32:12,370 --> 00:32:13,090
Substitute driver.

673
00:32:13,110 --> 00:32:13,950
What?

674
00:32:13,980 --> 00:32:15,170
Give me the car key.

675
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,050
You can't go.

676
00:32:18,420 --> 00:32:19,700
You and Haikuo need to stay here.

677
00:32:19,730 --> 00:32:20,850
It's a critical moment now.

678
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:22,150
We need to watch out for Qiu Lin and Mr. Song.

679
00:32:22,170 --> 00:32:23,370
They might cause trouble.

680
00:32:23,410 --> 00:32:24,030
Where are you going?

681
00:32:24,060 --> 00:32:25,140
I have an emergency.

682
00:32:25,170 --> 00:32:25,820
I'm sorry.

683
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:27,030
Let's meet again next time.

684
00:32:29,070 --> 00:32:30,300
You two, be safe.

685
00:32:30,340 --> 00:32:31,370
Drive carefully!

686
00:32:38,060 --> 00:32:39,910
My dad, I swear,

687
00:32:40,470 --> 00:32:42,660
he still gets so worked up over nothing at his age.

688
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,770
I can't stand him.

689
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:47,370
When you see him, watch your language, okay?

690
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,900
Don't start arguing again.

691
00:32:49,110 --> 00:32:52,090
If he's the one causing trouble, can't I say something?

692
00:32:52,530 --> 00:32:53,880
When people get old,

693
00:32:53,910 --> 00:32:54,990
they're like children again.

694
00:32:55,010 --> 00:32:56,300
They get agitated when you scold them.

695
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,810
Why isn't Grandpa Zhou like that?

696
00:32:59,390 --> 00:33:01,040
He's always so gentle and mild-mannered.

697
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:02,540
Your dad has a good temper too.

698
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:04,390
I've never seen him talk back.

699
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:06,130
My dad does talk back.

700
00:33:06,310 --> 00:33:08,580
He just mutters it so others can't hear it.

701
00:33:12,540 --> 00:33:13,440
I think

702
00:33:14,180 --> 00:33:15,680
I should take this opportunity

703
00:33:16,300 --> 00:33:17,340
to get them both to stop working

704
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:18,320
and retire soon.

705
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:20,300
Why should they retire?

706
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:22,940
I'm capable of supporting them now.

707
00:33:22,970 --> 00:33:25,390
They'll be happy that you're making money,

708
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:28,430
but their generation really can't stand being idle.

709
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:31,340
It's even more impossible for them to be comfortable spending their children's money.

710
00:33:31,370 --> 00:33:32,260
Why?

711
00:33:32,300 --> 00:33:34,700
Their joy comes from showing off.

712
00:33:34,820 --> 00:33:37,180
The more successful their children are, the happier they are.

713
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:38,240
A couple of years ago,

714
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:40,690
my mom used to complain to me.

715
00:33:41,380 --> 00:33:42,270
She said,

716
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:44,910
"When will I be able to enjoy the fruits of your success?"

717
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:47,320
Later, when I made some money and bought her jewelry,

718
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:49,670
she yelled my ear off.

719
00:33:49,690 --> 00:33:52,470
She said, "You should've saved this money for your dowry.

720
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:54,050
Your father and I are still young.

721
00:33:54,090 --> 00:33:55,440
You don't need to worry about us."

722
00:33:56,450 --> 00:33:57,770
How old are they?

723
00:33:57,810 --> 00:33:58,840
Still think they're young, huh?

724
00:34:00,050 --> 00:34:03,510
It's precisely because they've reached this age that they can't admit to being old.

725
00:34:03,860 --> 00:34:06,220
Otherwise, they'd really be old.

726
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:19,620
Let's go a bit faster.

727
00:34:37,460 --> 00:34:38,139
Mom.

728
00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:38,810
Mom.

729
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:40,530
Aunt Liang.

730
00:34:40,590 --> 00:34:41,940
You two came together?

731
00:34:41,969 --> 00:34:42,940
Well, I had some drinks,

732
00:34:42,969 --> 00:34:43,820
so I couldn't drive.

733
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:44,870
How's my dad?

734
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:47,270
Don't worry, the doctor said he's fine now.

735
00:34:47,290 --> 00:34:48,719
He got a dozen stitches on his stomach.

736
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:49,989
What happened?

737
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:51,810
Someone was stealing oil.

738
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:53,120
Your dad acted like the Good Samaritan

739
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:54,880
and pushed the thieves too far.

740
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:56,219
It's okay now.

741
00:34:56,250 --> 00:34:57,690
The doctor said he was treated in time.

742
00:34:56,810 --> 00:35:01,670
[Tianjin City People's Hospital]

743
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:01,080
He can be discharged after a few days of rest.

744
00:35:01,860 --> 00:35:02,750
Don't worry.

745
00:35:03,110 --> 00:35:04,110
Which ward?

