You're the one who's sick.

844
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:53,920
I told you before we came

845
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,780
to watch your language when you see your dad.

846
00:39:56,230 --> 00:39:58,420
You didn't listen, and we almost had another fight just now.

847
00:39:59,570 --> 00:40:00,620
What's wrong with having a fight?

848
00:40:01,030 --> 00:40:02,220
He was reckless.

849
00:40:02,390 --> 00:40:03,340
Can't I say that?

850
00:40:04,950 --> 00:40:06,710
That's just how your dad is.

851
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:09,020
He loves to meddle and stand up for others.

852
00:40:09,890 --> 00:40:11,150
He doesn't think he's wrong,

853
00:40:11,150 --> 00:40:12,430
but you insist on him admitting his mistake.

854
00:40:12,430 --> 00:40:13,710
Isn't that just asking for a fight?

855
00:40:14,300 --> 00:40:16,960
If he would listen, that'd be fine.

856
00:40:16,990 --> 00:40:18,390
The problem is that he can't change.

857
00:40:19,180 --> 00:40:20,260
Even if he can't change, he has to.

858
00:40:21,450 --> 00:40:22,200
Fine.

859
00:40:22,270 --> 00:40:23,070
Go ahead inside.

860
00:40:23,230 --> 00:40:24,260
You two have a fight.

861
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:26,640
Beat him into submission, then force him to admit he's wrong.

862
00:40:31,430 --> 00:40:32,950
Is this how you're supposed to give advice?

863
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:36,970
Eat.

864
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:38,510
I bought it for your mom.

865
00:40:39,180 --> 00:40:40,060
Have you eaten already?

866
00:40:40,230 --> 00:40:41,060
I'm full from anger.

867
00:40:48,810 --> 00:40:50,210
Don't provoke me.

868
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:54,550
Why didn't you bring me a bottle of water?

869
00:40:57,540 --> 00:40:58,360
Serves you right.

870
00:41:09,580 --> 00:41:11,680
The remaining few businesses have all signed as well.

871
00:41:13,170 --> 00:41:14,370
The task has been completed successfully.

872
00:41:14,940 --> 00:41:15,660
Good job.

873
00:41:17,950 --> 00:41:18,780
Where's Mr. Xie?

874
00:41:20,250 --> 00:41:21,910
He had something to attend to.

875
00:41:21,930 --> 00:41:22,520
He went to Tianjin.

876
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:23,360
Why?

877
00:41:23,490 --> 00:41:25,130
We're in the middle of a fierce battle with Yuntu right now

878
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:26,230
and he took time off?

879
00:41:26,300 --> 00:41:27,980
Does he not have any sense of organizational discipline?

880
00:41:30,050 --> 00:41:31,090
His father was hospitalized.

881
00:41:31,110 --> 00:41:32,390
So what if his father was hospitalized?

882
00:41:32,580 --> 00:41:33,950
Even if his father were dying right now,

883
00:41:33,980 --> 00:41:35,860
he couldn't just leave without saying a word.

884
00:41:35,890 --> 00:41:38,330
Just let us know if there's anything that needs to be done.

885
00:41:38,630 --> 00:41:39,620
We'll handle it.

886
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:41,310
These past few days,

887
00:41:41,460 --> 00:41:43,700
our market share has indeed increased,

888
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:46,370
but the number of orders has decreased.

889
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:47,510
That's impossible.

890
00:41:47,540 --> 00:41:49,460
So what if you had successful street canvassing?

891
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:50,440
So what

892
00:41:50,470 --> 00:41:51,540
if you signed agreements

893
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:52,910
with all the merchants?

894
00:41:52,950 --> 00:41:54,560
The merchants aren't placing orders now.

895
00:41:54,590 --> 00:41:55,660
What can you two do about it?

896
00:41:55,910 --> 00:41:57,390
Why aren't they placing orders?

897
00:41:57,790 --> 00:41:59,330
Yuntu has increased their subsidies.

898
00:41:59,890 --> 00:42:01,670
They're subsidizing an average of three yuan per order.

899
00:42:02,110 --> 00:42:03,090
They're crazy.

900
00:42:03,810 --> 00:42:05,000
How long can they keep burning money like this?

901
00:42:05,020 --> 00:42:06,220
That's why I've been telling you all along

902
00:42:06,260 --> 00:42:07,460
to quickly apply to headquarters

903
00:42:07,490 --> 00:42:08,890
for us to increase our subsidies as well.

904
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:13,480
Mr. Xie won't agree to that.

905
00:42:13,510 --> 00:42:14,190
For him to disagree,

906
00:42:14,190 --> 00:42:15,470
he has to be here, right?

907
00:42:15,650 --> 00:42:17,190
We can't just stand by and watch

908
00:42:17,190 --> 00:42:19,070
as Yuntu takes our territories one by one,

909
00:42:19,090 --> 00:42:20,700
without even the strength to fight back.

910
00:42:21,110 --> 00:42:21,990
Isn't that embarrassing?

911
00:42:22,620 --> 00:42:24,670
What will the entire industry think of us?

912
00:42:25,260 --> 00:42:25,740
Alright.

913
00:42:26,500 --> 00:42:27,440
How about this?

914
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:29,270
Let's put the subsidy issue

915
00:42:29,350 --> 00:42:30,540
on hold for now.

916
00:42:30,570 --> 00:42:32,160
Let's do what we can.

917
00:42:32,270 --> 00:42:34,220
Continue to optimize the delivery process,

918
00:42:34,250 --> 00:42:36,040
and further reduce the delivery time.

919
00:42:36,870 --> 00:42:38,000
Further reduce it?

920
00:42:38,020 --> 00:42:38,550
We're already at the limit.

921
00:42:38,550 --> 00:42:39,630
Leave it to us.

922
00:42:40,330 --> 00:42:41,020
We'll figure something out.

923
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:43,880
We'll give our all for the company.

924
00:42:45,750 --> 00:42:46,440
We can't.

925
00:42:47,730 --> 00:42:49,120
Hurry up.

926
00:42:53,750 --> 00:42:54,560
Brother-in-law,

927
00:42:55,170 --> 00:42:56,090
the illness

928
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,900
of Mr. Xie's father happened

929
00:42:57,980 --> 00:42:59,450
at quite an opportune time, didn't it?

930
00:43:02,630 --> 00:43:04,370
Stop looking.

